Description: Lead artefact, possibly a net weight in the form of a hollow ovoid blob with large irregular perforations on two sides and gnarled surface, similar in shape to a small closed bell.
Curator's comments: Maybe one of the lead "net sinkers" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76, though the item is not exactly U-shaped.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.81, p.186, pl.28)
